title: [@types/ws] Remove dependency on node >= 10
body:
Removes a dependency on `net.AddressInfo`, which is only present in `@types/node@10` and creates a dependency that is not needed.  Version 5.x of `ws` requires node 4.5+ and should not have this dependency: https://github.com/websockets/ws/releases/tag/5.0.0

The error you receive when using types for node versions below 10 is:

```
node_modules/@types/ws/index.d.ts:179:24 - error TS2694: Namespace '"net"' has no exported member 'AddressInfo'.
```

Two related issues exist: #25890 (closed) and #26195 (open).  The appropriate interface for the return type of the `server.address()` function is in fact the same as `net.AddressInfo | string` (docs here: https://github.com/websockets/ws/blob/master/doc/ws.md#serveraddress) so I have extracted the interface and included it in this definition to remove the dependency on node >= 10 types.

title: More robust Mocha definitions
body:
This adds some missing type information for "mocha" and fixes some incorrect type information in the current definitions:

- Removes `GenericEventEmitter` in favor of a forward declaration for `NodeJS.EventEmitter` (without requiring "node"). Also, `GenericEventEmitter` was declared as a class, which added it to the value space in the global scope.
- Adds typed events for `Runner`, `Runnable`, and `Suite`.
- Corrects the "exports" on `Mocha` for `Runnable`, `Context`, `Runner`, etc.
  - They were incorrectly "exported" as the instance type, not the constructor.
  - They were only "exported" as values, so type-space entities could not be resolved.
- Removed a few members that don't actually exist in source (i.e. `hasOnly`).
- Added overloads to disambiguate between `(done: (err?) => void) => void` and `() => PromiseLike<void>` for suite/test/hook callbacks as Mocha _does not_ allow you to use `done` in an async function callback.
- Moved browser-only extensions to `Mocha` (added in browser-entry.js) to the `BrowserMocha` interface, of which the global `mocha` variable is the only instance.
